); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Der Schöpfer:</span></p><p>Alex Hanimann (*1955) ist ein Schweizer Künstler und Professor für Visuelle Kommunikation an der Zürcher Hochschule der Künste. Sein Tätigkeitsbereich umfasst Zeichnungen, Malerei, Lettrismus, Druckgrafiken und Objektkunst.</p>','<h3>The Work</h3><p>Just like the artwork, &ldquo;Towers&rdquo;, at Escher-Wyss-Platz, the figure of &ldquo;Anne-Sophie&rdquo; was created within the framework of the art festival, &ldquo;Art and the City&rdquo;. The over 5-meter (16.4ft) tall chrome steel sculpture stands in front of the 25hours hotel Zurich-West. This larger-than-life figure was based on a real person who was a music student at the time and represents the youth of her generation and of the Zürich-West quarter.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Special Remarks</span></p><p>During the &ldquo;Art and the City&rdquo; art festival, &ldquo;Vanessa&rdquo; originally stood on Steinfelsplatz in Zürich-West. This figure became a kind of mascot for the festival. However, when this artwork was returned to its owner after the thee-month loan period, the artist, Alex Hanimann, immediately set about creating a second, permanent figure.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Location</span></p><p>&ldquo;Anne-Sophie&rdquo; stands in front of the 25hours hotel in Zürich-West and embodies the youth of both her generation and the quarter.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">The Creator</span></p><p>Alex Hanimann (born in 1955) is a Swiss artist and Professor of Visual Communication at Zurich University of the Arts. His field of activity focuses on drawings, paintings, Lettrism, graphic prints, and object art.</p>','<h3>L&rsquo;œuvre&nbsp;:</h3><p>Tout comme l&rsquo;œuvre Towers située place Escher-Wyss, la sculpture Anne-Sophie est née dans le cadre du festival Art and the City. La sculpture en acier chromé de plus de 5 mètres de haut se dresse devant l&rsquo;hôtel 25hours à Zurich-Ouest. Cette immense représentation d&rsquo;une ancienne étudiante en musique représente la jeunesse de sa génération et celle du quartier Zurich-Ouest.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Particularités&nbsp;:</span></p><p>Pendant le festival Art and the City, une autre sculpture érigée sur la Steinfelsplatz à Zurich-Ouest est devenue la mascotte du festival&nbsp;: &laquo;&nbsp;Vanessa&nbsp;&raquo;. Après avoir été mise à disposition de la ville pendant trois mois, cette œuvre devait être rendue à son propriétaire. L&rsquo;artiste Alex Hanimann a donc commencé immédiatement une deuxième sculpture qui restera en place.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Emplacement&nbsp;:</span></p><p>Devant l&rsquo;hôtel 25hours à Zurich-Ouest, &laquo;&nbsp;Anne-Sophie&nbsp;&raquo; symbolise la jeunesse du quartier et de sa génération.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Le créateur&nbsp;:</span></p><p>Alex Hanimann (*1955) est un artiste suisse et professeur de communication visuelle à la Haute école des arts de Zurich. Dessins, peinture, lettrisme, impression graphique et art objet emplissent sa sphèred&rsquo;activités.</p>','<h3>L&rsquo;opera</h3><p>Proprio come l&rsquo;opera Towers sulla Escher-Wyss-Platz, anche Anne-Sophie è nata nell&rsquo;ambito del festival Art and the City. La scultura in acciaio cromato si trova davanti al 25hours Hotel Zürich-West ed è alta oltre 5 metri. Questa copia sovradimensionata di una ex studentessa di musica rappresenta la gioventù della sua generazione, ma anche quella del quartiere Zürich-West.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Particolarità</span></p><p>Durante il festival Art and the City, fu &ldquo;Vanessa&rdquo; a trovare posto per prima sulla Steinfelsplatz di Zürich-West, diventando una sorta di mascotte dell&rsquo;evento. Dato che, dopo un prestito di tre mesi, la scultura tornò al proprietario, l&rsquo;artista Alex Hanimann iniziò a realizzarne subito una seconda, permanente.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Luogo</span></p><p>Davanti al 25hours Hotel Zürich-West, &ldquo;Anne-Sophie&rdquo; simboleggia la gioventù del quartiere e della sua generazione.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">L&rsquo;autore</span></p><p>Alex Hanimann (*1955) è un artista svizzero e professore di comunicazione visiva all&rsquo;Istituto Superiore di Arte di Zurigo. Si occupa di disegni, pittura, Lettrismo, riproduzioni a stampa e arte oggettuale.</p>','Anne-Sophie – Alex Hannimann','“Anne-Sophie” by Alex Hanimann','Anne-Sophie – Alex Hannimann','Anne-Sophie – Alex Hannimann','In Zürich-West glänzt und spiegelt die Chromstahlplastik Anne-Sophie von Künstler Alex Hanimann.','The chrome steel sculpture, “Anne-Sophie”, by Alex Hanimann shines and reflects in Zürich-West. ','La sculpture en acier chromé Anne-Sophie de l’artiste Alex Hanimann brille et miroite à Zurich-Ouest.','A Zürich-West, la scultura Anne-Sophie dell’artista Alex Hanimann luccica e rispecchia immagini.',NULL,'https://cdn.zuerich.com/sites/default/files/web_zuerich_anne_sophie_1280x960_21988.jpg','2018-06-04 11:49:41 +0200','Im Trendquartier Zürich-West','Located in the trendy Zürich-West quarter','Dans le quartier branché Zurich-Ouest','Nel quartiere di tendenza di Zürich-West',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CH','Zürich',8005,'Pfingstweidstrasse 102',NULL,NULL,'https://www.zuerich.com/node/227374',47.391037300000,8.509409200000,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'POINT (47.3910373 8.5094092)',5,'https://cdn.zuerich.com/sites/default/files/web_zuerich_anne_sophie_1280x960_21979.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
